<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Endangered & Threatened Animals</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #FFD1AA;
            font-size: 18px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #003333;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #162955;
        }
        .endangered {
            color: red;
        }
        .threatened {
            color: OrangeRed;
        }
        .scientific-name {
            font-style: italic;
        }
        img {
            height: 150px;
        }
        #armadillo-img {
            border-style: solid;
        }
        #gray-bat-img {
            border-style: dashed;
        }
        #grizzly-img {
            border-style: dotted;
        }
        #nle-bat-img {
            border-style: double;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>this is a h1 tag i guess bro</h1>

    <h2>Giant Armadillo</h2>
    <ul>
        <li class="scientific-name">Scientific name: <em>Priodontes maximus</em></li>
        <li>Home range: South America</li>
        <li class="endangered">Status: Endangered</li>
    </ul>
    <img id="armadillo-img" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/67/Giant_armadillo_Florentino.jpg/320px-Giant_armadillo_Florentino.jpg" alt="Giant Armadillo">
    <p><small>Photo: Associação Pró-Carnívoros, via Wikimedia Commons</small></p>

    <h2>Gray Bat</h2>
    <ul>
        <li class="scientific-name">Scientific name: <em>Myotis grisescens</em></li>
        <li>Home range: Central and southeastern United States</li>
        <li class="endangered">Status: Endangered</li>
    </ul>
    <img id="gray-bat-img" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Myotis_grisescens.jpg/320px-Myotis_grisescens.jpg" alt="Gray Bat">
    <p><small>Photo: USFWS, via Wikimedia Commons</small></p>

    <h2>Grizzly Bear</h2>
    <ul>
        <li class="scientific-name">Scientific name: <em>Ursus arctos horribilis</em></li>
        <li>Home range: Holarctic (North America)</li>
        <li class="threatened">Status: Threatened</li>
    </ul>
    <img id="grizzly-img" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/GrizzlyBearJeanBeaufort.jpg/320px-GrizzlyBearJeanBeaufort.jpg" alt="Grizzly Bear">
    <p><small>Photo: Jean Beaufort, via Wikimedia Commons</small></p>

    <h2>Northern Long-Eared Bat</h2>
    <ul>
        <li class="scientific-name">Scientific name: <em>Myotis septentrionalis</em></li>
        <li>Home range: Eastern United States and Canada</li>
        <li class="threatened">Status: Threatened</li>
    </ul>
    <img id="nle-bat-img" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Myotis_septentrionalis_crop.jpg/320px-Myotis_septentrionalis_crop.jpg" alt="Northern Long-Eared Bat">
    <p><small>Photo: USFWS, via Wikimedia Commons</small></p>

</body>
</html>
